{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nWith many attestations every consumer must address a specific kind; today verify reads the single slot.\n## What\nMigrate `verify_signature()` internals to read `state[\"attestations\"][kind]` (with legacy\n`state[\"signature\"]` fold-in) instead of the single slot. `verify_signature(ticket_id,\nkind=...)` certifies one kind; with no kind it returns a `{kind: verdict}` map. Migrate the\ncallers that chain through it to pass an explicit kind: `claim_gate_check`,\n`drift_refresh_candidate`, `refresh_attestation` (attest.py), `_child_closure_findings`\n(completion.py) [gate-semantics owned by 929e], and the CLI/MCP entrypoints. CLI: `--kind K`\nis the single-gate exit-code form (exit 0 iff certified); no `--kind` lists all (exit 0 iff\nall certified). SCOPE BOUNDARY: this story owns the `verify_signature` MCP tool + its result\nschema; the `attestations` field in the ticket-state MCP response is owned by ed26.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/signing.py` (`verify_signature`, `verify_signature_cli`), `src/rebar/mcp_server.py`\n(verify tool only), `src/rebar/schemas/verify_signature_result.schema.json`.\n## Depends on\nRequires 114f merged (reads `state[\"attestations\"]`).\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `verify_signature()` reads `attestations[kind]` (legacy fold-in), not the single slot.\n- [ ] `verify_signature(ticket_id, kind=...)` returns one verdict; no-kind returns `{kind: verdict}`.\n- [ ] CLI `--kind K` exit 0 iff that kind certified; no `--kind` lists all, exit 0 iff all certified.\n- [ ] Callers migrated to explicit kind: claim_gate_check, drift_refresh_candidate, refresh_attestation, _child_closure_findings, CLI/MCP.\n- [ ] Legacy single-signature ticket verifies under its derived kind."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782784432883295001,"uuid":"a9326de7-fc1b-44ea-b0ef-52c4abb2eccd"}